quran[26]{c,v,t}:
  27,56,"But the answer of his people was only to say, 'Drive out Lot's family from your city! verily, they are a folk who would keep pure"
  27,57,"But we saved him and his family except his wife, her we destined to be of those who lingered"
  27,58,"and we rained down upon them rain, and evil was the rain of those who were warned"
  27,59,"Say, 'Praise belongs to God; and peace be upon His servants whom He has chosen! Is God best, or what they associate with Him"
  27,60,"He who created the heavens and the earth; and sends down upon you from the heaven water; and we cause to grow therewith gardens fraught with beauty; ye could not cause the trees thereof to grow! Is there a god with God? nay, but they are a people who make peers with Him"
  27,61,"He who made the earth, settled, and placed amongst it rivers; and placed upon it firm mountains; and placed between the two seas a barrier; is there a god with God? nay, but most of them know not"
  27,62,He who answers the distressed when he calls upon Him and removes the evil; and makes you successors in the earth; is there a god with God? little is it that ye are mindful
  27,63,"He who guides you in the darkness, of the land and of the sea; and who sends winds as glad tidings before His mercy; is there a god with God? exalted be God above what they associate with Him"
  27,64,He who began the creation and then will make it return again; and who provides you from the heaven and the earth; is there a god with God? so bring your proofs if ye do speak the truth
  27,65,"Say, 'None in the heavens or the earth know the unseen save only God; but they perceive not when they shall be raised"
  27,66,"nay, but their knowledge attains to somewhat of the hereafter; nay, but they are in doubt concerning it! nay, but they are blind"
  27,67,"And those who disbelieved said, 'What! when we have become dust and our fathers too, shall we indeed be brought forth"
  27,68,"We were promised this, we and our fathers before us, this is nothing but old folks' tales"
  27,69,"Say, 'Journey on through the land and see how was the end of the sinners"
  27,70,"and grieve not for them, and be not straitened at what they plot"
  27,71,"They say, 'When shall this threat be if ye do tell the truth"
  27,72,"Say, 'It may be that there is pressing close behind you a part of what ye would hasten on"
  27,73,"But, verily, thy Lord is full of grace to men, but most of them will not be thankful"
  27,74,"and, verily, thy Lord knows what their breasts conceal and what they manifest"
  27,75,"and there is no secret thing in the heaven or the earth, save that it is in the perspicuous Book"
  27,76,"Verily, this Qur'an relates to the people of Israel most of that whereon they do dispute"
  27,77,"and, verily, it is a guidance and a mercy to the believers"
  27,78,"Verily, thy Lord decides between them by His judgment, for He is mighty, knowing"
  27,79,"Rely thou then upon God, verily, thou art standing on obvious truth"
  27,80,"Verily, thou canst not make the dead to hear, and thou canst not make the deaf to hear the call when they turn their backs on thee"
  27,81,"nor art thou a guide to the blind, out of their error: thou canst only make to hear such as believe in our signs, and such as are resigned"